This is now version 0.0.4pre3 of KGGZ.

News - what has changed?:
-beep implemented (from Xlib)
-login now distinguishes between login types
-join/leave is implemented in both the players list and the chat
-config.h for cleaning up the sources
-a new logo, hopefully not promising too much wrong things
-now all 3 clients in kde menu
-server profiles
-settings are used and saved
-optionally: FTP connection for game updates
-optionally: KHTML as browser widget (superseding the quickhelp), with shortlinks; enables Java game modules
-optionally: Server (ggzd) control via fork, exec, signal.h & co.
-i18n support does now cover all files, and implemented in Makefile (currently only German)
-icons in the menus, and shown in window manager
-visual Grubby dialog

Requirements:
-Xlib for the beep
-Qt 2.2.1
-KDE 2.0 (kdelibs should be sufficient)
-KHTML (optionally) for the browser
-Qt network extension (optionally) for FTP

Directory structure:
/ - sources
/images/ - images for kggz
/images/games/ - icons for all game modules
/images/icons/ - menu & widget icons
/images/wm/ - window manager decoration, e.g. start menu & desktop
/doc/ - documentation
/doc/html - tbd: detailed programmer information on kggz
/help/ - local in-client help files
/po/ - i18n files

Installation structure:
~/.kde/share/locale/l10n/... - i18n .mo files
~/.kde/share/icons/ - icons for KDE
~/.kde/share/applnk/Games/ggz/ - KDE menu entries
~/.kde/share/mimelnk/application/ - Zone entry
destdir/bin/ - executable
destdir/share/kggz/... - core client data

You can do the following things:
-invoke the server and/or connect to it
-chat
-browse the rooms list
-use the chat with all commands
**attempt to join or launch a game
**see your network lag
-browse the internet :-)
-download game modules
**configure game modules
**talk with grubby
** means: todo, but already prepared

You can't do yet:
-play games

What else needs to be done?
-documentation (html)
-port some of the games to kde (although one can use gtk+ games, of course)
-more more games for ggz!!!

